imer on plan evaluation practice and an original contribution to theory, Evaluating Urban and Regional Plans is an invaluable resource not only for the Canadian planning community but for planners everywhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCity planningzCanadaxEvaluation. 0aRegional planningzCanadaxEvaluation. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311141764640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486627940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774866279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774866279/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-141764-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles